<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-101-079 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 049 425</DOCID><JOURNAL>San Jose Mercury News  July 29 1991 p1D(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Zeroing in: Trimble's target: Fortune 500. (Charles Trimble,president and CEO of Trimble Navigation Ltd.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Langberg, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Charles R. Trimble is founder of Trimble Navigation Ltd,Sunnyvale, CA.andP;  His goal is to build Trimble Navigation into aFortune 500 Company.andP;  Financial analysts say this is reasonablebased on sales that have doubled each year for the past threeyears.andP;  Trimble Navigation is a leader in the development of theGlobal Positioning System (GPS), a US Air Force satellite networkthat allows receivers on earth to instantly measure longitude andlatitude accurately to within 50 feet.andP;  GPS receivers were used bythe troops during the Persian Gulf crisis.andP;  Trimble Navigationdoubled its sales in the first part of 1991 by filling rush ordersfrom the US Army for the hand-held GPS receivers.andP;  Trimble offeredstock in his company, starting in 1990, and the stock is currentlyworth $15.50 per share.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Trimble Navigation Ltd. (Management).andO;Topic:     Goals and ObjectivesStrategic PlanningManagement StyleNavigationSatellite CommunicationsStockChief Executive OfficersUnited States. Air Force.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andO;Person:    Trimble, Charles R. (Management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>